# 🚀 DevOps End-to-End CI/CD Pipeline

## 📘 Project Overview
This project implements a **complete CI/CD workflow** using **Jenkins**, **Docker**, **Ansible**, and **Kubernetes**.  
It automates the process of:
1. Pulling source code from GitHub  
2. Building and tagging Docker images on the Ansible server  
3. Pushing the image to Docker Hub  
4. Copying deployment files to the Kubernetes server  
5. Deploying the latest version to the Kubernetes cluster  

---

## 🧩 Technologies Used
- **Jenkins** – Continuous Integration and Deployment
- **Ansible Server (13.71.29.243)** – Docker image build and versioning
- **Kubernetes Server (74.225.175.155)** – Application deployment
- **Docker Hub (madival)** – Image registry
- **GitHub Repository:** [Devops_Project](https://github.com/supriyarajkumar27/Devops_Project.git)

---

## ⚙️ CI/CD Workflow Summary

### 1️⃣ Git Checkout
- Jenkins clones the source code from GitHub using the repository URL.
- This ensures the latest application code is always fetched before build.

```groovy
stage("Git Checkout") {
  git 'https://github.com/supriyarajkumar27/Devops_Project.git'
}
